# SPA history fallback. Cloudflare Pages serves real files first ONLY for paths
# that no _redirects rule matches — a 200-rewrite rule (proxy) is evaluated
# before the real file and wins even when a file exists at the requested path.
# So a broad /bombsquad/* 200 rewrite would shadow the real /bombsquad/assets/*
# bundle files and serve the SPA index HTML in their place. Asset pass-through
# rules must therefore be declared explicitly and ordered before the broad
# fallback (see the /bombsquad/assets/* rule below).
#
# Legacy pre-split paths. Before BombSquad moved under /bombsquad/, these
# root-level paths were served by the BombSquad SPA. The platform shell now owns
# the root and has no routes for them, so a hard-load would 404. Permanently
# redirect each to its canonical /bombsquad/ path. Listed first so these
# specific 301s win over the SPA fallbacks below.
/game /bombsquad/ 301
/game/connect /bombsquad/connect 301
/game/run /bombsquad/run 301
/result /bombsquad/result 301
/compatibility /bombsquad/compatibility 301
# BombSquad is a separate sub-app (BrowserRouter under /bombsquad/), so its deep
# client routes (/bombsquad/connect, /bombsquad/run, /bombsquad/result, …) must
# fall back to the BombSquad index, not the platform shell.
#
# Two rules, in order:
#   1. Pass real asset requests through to themselves (200 to the same path).
#      Vite emits every built asset under /bombsquad/assets/, so this protects
#      the JS/CSS bundle. Because the broad fallback below is a 200 rewrite that
#      would otherwise shadow these real files (serving index HTML with a
#      text/html content-type and breaking the whole bundle), this MUST come
#      first.
#   2. Fall every other /bombsquad/ deep route back to the BombSquad index. The
#      target is the directory /bombsquad/, NOT /bombsquad/index.html: Cloudflare
#      Pages auto-redirects an index-file request to its extension-less directory
#      form (/bombsquad/index.html -> 308 -> /bombsquad/), so an index-file
#      target produces a redirect that drops to the platform shell. Targeting the
#      directory serves the SPA index cleanly with no canonicalization bounce.
# Both rules precede the catch-all so the more specific /bombsquad/ prefix wins.
/bombsquad/assets/* /bombsquad/assets/:splat 200
/bombsquad/* /bombsquad/ 200
# Botanical Garden is a separate sub-app (BrowserRouter under /botanical/, base
# /botanical/, deep route /botanical/manual), so it needs the same two rules as
# BombSquad — asset pass-through FIRST (or the broad 200 rewrite shadows the real
# /botanical/assets/* bundle and serves index HTML in its place), then the SPA
# fallback to the /botanical/ directory (NOT /botanical/index.html, which would
# 308-bounce to the platform shell). Oracle / Shadow Chase are HashRouter and
# need no such guard (their deep routes live in the #-fragment, never hitting the
# server), which is why only BombSquad and Botanical appear here.
/botanical/assets/* /botanical/assets/:splat 200
/botanical/* /botanical/ 200
# Everything else falls back to the platform shell (BrowserRouter at the root).
/* /index.html 200
